column56: Kinda simplistic and rather superficial. also repetitive. makes interpretation beyond ""youre a star"" kinda difficult.
lot of weird words, also random spanish words that make no sense in the context of the song. very weird all around.
I know its Rihanna and the song is one of her first big songs, a cookie cutter pop song about getting up and dancing. Not much to really be wrong about interpreting.
a little simplistic and they could easily be perceived as about sexual situations as they are about something more deep.
not difficult, seems very ""stuck in a rut, my life sucks, its just the same thing different day""
Weird lyrics, almost seemed like a love song in a weird way but at the same time it comes across as hedonistic.
A little too abstract but it seems to be directed at someone who got too big to their bridges or however the saying goes.
A little abstract but it was a calling nonetheless so i kinda get it.
Nothing specific. maybe the word porgy?
No i think the message was pretty clear. It was a shout out to other artists who the singer feels has it wrong in their approach.
the words are very weird and vague and open to interpretation. maybe a love story gone wrong, idk tbh.
It just came across as vague even though the words werent complicated. Nature? Love? a little a both. idk to be honest. a little too abstract for me.
its very ""fuck bitches get money"" extremely transparent.
Nothing stood out but i feel like the words could be applied to different types of scenarios and symbols not just a person like it is on the surface level.
